  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "folder 55 - 006\nC-6\n\nI knew this was the payoff revelation! But it took me years to see how it applies directly to 2-74 [+ the meta-abstraction + anamnesis, because it was not until one year ago -Feb '81- that I at last explicated the meta-abstraction in words!]. If Gnosticism is the case we are in a prison + there is an evil demiurge who keeps us ignorant at all costs, because as Valentinean Gnosticism teaches, ignorance per se is the very ontological basis of our condition of thrall; + convers",
      "matched_alias": "Maitreya",
      "term_id": "TERM_maitreya",
      "term_name": "Maitreya",
      "term_slug": "maitreya"
    },
    {
      "text": "Indexed\nfolder 55 - 007\nC-7\n\nit is fundamental in Gnosticism that the whole prison is to keep the sparks of light (1) ignorant; + (2) here (imprisoned), + this endless horizontal tracking does both: we stay here forever – not for a lifetime but for eternity! Ach, Gott! Vatter! Forever. Like a time-travel story: like, specifically \"A Little Something for Us Tempunauts\"! It is forever; when we die we just start tracking over (but things look different; note \"look different\" – not \"change.\" Oh God,",
      "matched_alias": "Maitreya",
      "term_id": "TERM_maitreya",
      "term_name": "Maitreya",
      "term_slug": "maitreya"
    },
    {
      "text": "Indexed\nfolder 55 - 007\nC-7\n\nit is fundamental in Gnosticism that the whole prison is to keep the sparks of light (1) ignorant; + (2) here (imprisoned), + this endless horizontal tracking does both: we stay here forever – not for a lifetime but for eternity! Ach, Gott! Vatter! Forever. Like a time-travel story: like, specifically \"A Little Something for Us Tempunauts\"! It is forever; when we die we just start tracking over (but things look different; note \"look different\" – not \"change.\" Oh God,",
      "matched_alias": "Yaldabaoth",
      "term_id": "TERM_yaldabaoth",
      "term_name": "Yaldabaoth",
      "term_slug": "yaldabaoth"
    }
